Description: Agentless hardening of Ubuntu and Debian servers
 Castellan applies CIS/ANSSI-style security hardening to Ubuntu and Debian
 servers over SSH, driven by Ansible from your own machine. It runs a read-only
 audit and an idempotent apply with strict anti-lockout ordering, selectable
 hardening profiles (minimal/standard/paranoid) and an interactive setup.
 .
 Nothing is installed on the target: only SSH and the pre-existing Python 3 are
 used. Ansible core 2.16 or newer is recommended on the control machine.

